an automatic grading scheme for simple programming exercises a discussion is given of alterations that were made to a typical university operating system  to record the results of programming exercises in three different languages including assembly language   in this computercontrolled grading scheme provision is made for testing with programmersupplied data  and for final runs with systemsupplied data  exercises run under the scheme may be mixed with other  programs and no special recognition of exercises by the operators is necessary cacm may 1969 hext j b winings j w 